 :b: DRAWING METHOD :b:
------------------------------------
FONT: https://www.fonts4free.net/laffayette-comic-pro-font.html
PASSIVE EXERCISE: practice while going to bathroom
	(mentally draw something in room in room (towels/tiles/etc)) 
FOR ANIMATING: animate ONE LINE AT A TIME:
	-- literally draw ALL movement OF ONE LINE, frame by frame, 
		Then move on to next line. 
COMPOSITION TRICKS:
	-- mentally 'draw' rough compositions (super low res)
		till one 'clicks'
	-- practice mentally drawing composition till it looks good
		drawn in the mind multiple times.
	--CLOTHS: 'YXZ' method- folds look like there
		are 'y/x/z's under the folds pushing
		them up (can look up method) 
	-- 3 points/triangle composition (tezuka method):
		choice 3 points of focus, 
		should be a triangle, sides can be different lengths
	-- use a mirror to test expressions/ hand positions/etc.
	-- exaggerate expressions if going cartoon
	-- use any visual shorthand/stereotypes/hints with what is in
		characters hand/around them to tell a story with picture.
	-- use exploding text/captions/etc. (ANY special effects,
		think old comics) 
	-- 's' curve/parabola/ spiral (loomis)
		the idea is have the underlying composition have
		these shapes in it. (gives a major 'pop') 
	-- Kim Jung Gi perspective:
		draw one 'plane', and project all other planes
		in relation to that one (easier mentally than 3 point)
	-- Kim Jung Gi cloth/armor:
		give cloth/armor/etc volume projected OUT from
		whoever is wearing it (make it thick) 
	-- Studio Gibli colorization (can be patterns/greyscale):
		%60 primary color
		%30 secondary color
		%10 accents
	-- have all things point to a focal point 
		(if a comic, lead to next panel) 
-----------------------
---- ACTUAL DRAWING:
------------------------
DRAW WITH BOTH HANDS,
GRIP PEN SUPER RELAXED AND TOWARDS CENTER OF PEN
	-- this reduces strain. 
	-- wrap wrist (bandana works ) for long sessions.
I put a few phone-scanner apps in the computer section,
hopefully one works good enough. 
----------------
-----PRACTICE:
----------------------- 
FOR DRAWING:
	-- first off, practice with non-dominate hand
		till OK with it (AFTER/ DURING 
		LEARNING WITH DOMINATE)
	-- practice drawing without guides
		(Kim-jung-ji style)
	-- practice drawing with BOTH HANDS AT ONCE
	(that is the goal, at least, mostly working)
FOR MENTAL GAME:
	(NOTE: for practicing/drawing, do NOT 
		look at refrences during drawing/
		mental drawing or between 3x sets (below))
	-- practice drawing in mind 
		(literally line by line image drawing
			something as if drawing by had)
	-- shoot for 3-'perfect' mind drawings without 
		looking for practice. 
	-- ONLY THEN try drawing it with pens. 
	(the first few mind drawings a day are harder)
FOR MENTAL GAME FOR MAKING ORIGINAL STUFF:
	Kim Jung Gi looked at stuff from multiple angles,
		mentally. 
	That worked, but the other method a lot of people
	use is focusing on 
	DRAWING MULTIPLE ROUGHS AND SEEING WHICH LOOKS GOOD
	(This can be done mentally, drawing in mind 
		with very few details several 'rough' 
		drafts (just outline works) 
		and picking best) 
FOR REFERENCES: 
	A mirror is super useful ( a 'selfi-convex-mirror' works too)
	Can always use references if helpful. 
WHAT TO PRACTICE: 
	What is interesting, anything to keep it interesting.
	Some artists books (loomis/'how to draw marvel comics'/etc)
	are excellent. 
	




 :b: COOKING (fast) methods :b:
-----------------------------------
I like to try to optimize cooking, the following
are a few optimized cooking methods I have found 
worked. Listing all the ways that did not work 
would be a much bigger list. 
NOTE: these are optimized methods,
traditional cooking is typically superior
-----------------------------------
-- BASELINE:
----------------------------------
-- in a pinch- 100% dark chocolate (carry a bar, it lasts super long)
-- wheatgrass juice- get powder, it works. (2x a day)
-- vitamin c 500mg (great for tendons) plus omega 3 1x a day. 
-----------------------------------
-- TRAVEL FOOD:
-------------------------------------
-- sandwiches/wraps or whatever is around
-- (crackers and non perishable junk food works,
--	not super healthy but doesn't go bad)
------------------
-- CURRENT RECIPES/COOKING STYLES:
------------------
-------------------------------
--- BLENDER: use a portable/single serving one,
---		drink out of blender itself, 
---		otherwise more stuff to clean
-------------------------------
-- COLD SOAK
-----------------------------
----	Generally, this is a bad idea, 
----		(which I tried for years getting to work)
----	stick with sandwiches/etc instead, don't eat as much. 
---- 	a lot of weird stuff like pretzels work, 
---- 		but the problem is cold-soaking isn't great
---- 		on stomach: 100% dark chocolate or sandwiches 
----		work better.
----	THE ONE EXCEPTION IS SLIGHTLY DAMPENED BREAD: it's different,
---		but filling (if you can get into it) 
-------------------------------
-- MICROWAVE
--------------------------------
---- Dampen any bread/etc before it goes in microwave
---- 	(keeps it from drying out)
---- FOR STUFF LIKE CORN TORTILLAS, THESE PLUS BEANS (CANNED)
----	MAKES AN EXCELLENT 'TAMALE' ISH-THING (again, moisten tortillas)
---- ALSO:
---- vegetables come out GREAT in microwave 
---- (sandwich melts can be made in advance for breakfast,
----	sliced bread + hardboiled egg quartered + cheese, 60 seconds) 
-------------------------------
-- HEAT AND WRAP IN TOWEL METHOD (cotton towels only):
--------------
----- BASICS: bring to boil, wrap pan leave in towel, come back later. 
----- 		(30 minutes, 1 hour)
----- WHY IT WORKS: It's slow cooking, idea is 'thermos cooking', 
-----		but works MUCH better with an actual pan, 
-----		a cotton towel (maybe on a potholder, too) is all that is 
-----		needed to keep food hot enough to keep cooking
----- WHY COOK LIKE THIS: 
-----		It's carefree, heat, set, walk away, come back with food.
-----------------
--  WHAT WORKS:
--------
-- OATMEAL: 1 part oats/3 parts water, NOT NEED TO STIR!!
--		(30 minutes to 1 hour)
--		Oats tend to be cooked under hydrated, this solves that
---------
-- PASTA: this is hit and miss, pasta should be up too water level,
--	and easier to put IN the sauce (again, not positive of ratio)
--	(oddly enough, beyond typical red/white sauces, 
--		savory peanut butter sauce with garlic is bomb here)
---------
-- INSTANT RICE/ BEANS:- note, CANNED beans, 
--	Instant rice cooked like this can take up 2-3x the water,
--	comes out much more 'plump. Good with a bit of pasta in it. 
----------
-- HARDBOILED EGG: POUR HOT WATER -OVER- EGGS, THEN BRING BACK TO BOIL
--	before warping in towel. 
--	(pouring boiling water OVER cold eggs for the 
--		initial 'adding-heat' bit is better as dropping
--		eggs in boiling water can break them, 
--		and the heat-shock is needed to loosen shell)
--	(I haven't tested the 'wrap up and forget it' cooking method 
--		with this, but supposedly works without the towel. 
--		It did work great in an actual thermos)
------------
-- GRITS -SHOULD- work great, but haven't tried them
-------------






